postcontent:
This is a mint Remington 700 stainless Rocky Mountain Elk Foundation commemorative rifle in 7mm Remington Ultra Magnum caliber.  The 7mm RUM is hard to tame, but this one is a pussycat with the Muscle Brake installed by Ryan Pierce at Piercision Rifles (http://www.piercisionrifles.com/brakes/).  The camo stock is in as-new condition.  Also included is a very nice set of Leupold split bases with 1" rings, and the front ring is a 1" offset version.  The recoil is equivalent to my .270 Rem shooting factory loads.  Best of all, this rifle is extremely accurate.  I purchased it from the original owner, who fired it 9 times (he gave me the remaining box of ammo).  I have fired it 18 times using a variety of factory ammo.  The rifle shot them all well, but the Remington Scirroco 150-gn round produced a 1/2" 3-shot group off of sandbags.  So you are buying a rifle with only 27 rounds down the pipe, not some ragged-out barrel.

The condition is excellent, but it's not perfect.  Perfect comes new in a box from Remington.  It has one small scratch on the floorplate, and one light scuff on the right side of the barrel about 2" back from the brake.  That's it.  The barrel was cut down slightly to 24-3/4" before adding the brake.  Overall barrel length from the receiver is 25-3/8" and overall length of the rifle is 46-1/4".

Local pick-up is always good.  I will only ship this to your FFL with a valid, signed FFL in hand.  Shipping is $30 in the lower 48.  If you need an integrity check, look me up on Ebay at Scottielover1.  I'm also selling an as-new Swarovski Habicht 4-12x50mm matte scope with Plex reticle in another Armslist listing.

Write me with your questions.  I can email you 20 photos of the rifle showing every side and angle.  Or feel free to call 33four-four five six-911four.  You can't go wrong with this 7mm RUM.  I also have some ammo that we can discuss as part of a deal.  Thanks for looking.
